observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Management the following courses of action:
Refrain from using the 5% LDRRMF for expenditure items that are not directly related to disaster prevention and mitigation, preparedness, response, and rehabilitation and recovery;
Provide adequate funding for the regular operating expenses of the MDRRMO particularly for the repair and maintenance of motor vehicles;
Submit a written explanation on the charges made to LDRRMF, which are not in line with PPAs mentioned in RA 10121 and NDRRMC-DBM-DILG JMC No. 2013-1; and
Submit the PhilGEPS registration numbers of the bidders for the procurements made through alternative methods pertinent to LDRRM Fund. For CY 2022 and ensuing years, to strictly follow the provisions of RA 9184.

a. Ensure that utilization of the  LGDF  is  in  accordance  with  the
   approved budget;


     b. Charges against the LGDF should be limited to the implementation of
        development  projects  and  refrain  from  use  of  the  same   for
        administrative and regular operating expenses;



   c. Justify the deficiencies noted in the procurement of spare  parts  and
      fuel;



   d.    Submit    the    necessary    lacking    documents     to     avoid
      suspension/disallowance.

a. Review the details of the Due to Local  Government  Units  account  to
      determine possible errors in recording of transactions  that  resulted
      to negative account balances and incorrect classification of accounts;


   b. Effect adjusting  journal  entries  to  reflect  the  correct  account
      balance;


   c. Facilitate the remittance of the Provincial and Barangay share in  RPT
      and Community  Tax  taking  into  consideration  those  that  remained
      outstanding from prior years;


   d. Adopt an effective set of internal control/s on recording the
      transactions relating to liability accounts.
